<h2>About the Vegetable RIC</h2>
<p align="left">The UC Vegetable Research and Information Center (Vegetable RIC) was organized to provide a statewide program to which all University of California personnel with any research or extension activities related to vegetable production, postharvest handling, marketing or consumption could affiliate. A second primary purpose to provide the vegetable industry, related industries, and others interested in vegetables, with a focal point to which they could obtain information and establish appropriate linkages with the University. The expected results are improved effectiveness and efficiency within UC; and improved collaboration, linkage and communication between UC and the vegetable industry, and between UC and other interested vegetable constituencies.   

<p align="left">The Director of the Vegetable RIC provides leadership to accomplish short and long term goals; convenes and leads internal and external committees to determine Center priorities, and develops and implements strategies for addressing those priorities. Past Directors: Ron Voss (1995-1998), Don Nevins (1999-2006) and Tim Hartz (May 2007-June 2017).<br>
      <br>
      Vegetable RIC Staff <br>
	<ul>
	  <li><em>Steve Fennimore</em>, Director, Vegetable RIC</a> (July 1, 2017-present)</li>
